name: The Ways of Artists
description: "To art one sets too tight a boundary if one demands that only an orderly, morally balanced soul has the right to express itself in it. As in the plastic arts, so in music and poetry, there is the art of the ugly soul along with the art of the beautiful soul; and the most powerful acts of art-the ability to shake souls, to make stones move, and to turn beasts into people-maybe it was this kind of art that succeeded best."  Friedrich Nietzsche
